 Investments




 Details Hidden



Westwing GmbH

                                    Westwing GmbH provides online shopping platform for home and living. The firm specializes in the marketing and retail distribution of home accessories and furniture at discounted prices, which can only be availed by the site’s registered members. Its product offerings include tables, sofas, beds, lamps, bathroom fixtures, and garden equipment and accessories. It also offers a lifestyle magazine, giving subscribers access to information on home design trend and tips. The company was founded by Delia Fischer, Georg Biersack, Tim Schäfer, Matthias Siepe, Alan Poensgehn, Benno Zerlin, and Stefan Smalla in 2011 and is headquartered in Munich, Germany.                                





 Details Hidden



Oxford Nanopore Technologies Ltd.

                                    Oxford Nanopore Technologies Ltd. develops proprietary technology platform for the electronic analysis of single molecules. It also develops instruments like GridIONTM and MinIONTM which are adaptable for the analysis of DNA, RNA, proteins, small molecules and other types of molecule. The firm's platform has a broad range of potential applications, including scientific research, personalized medicine, crop science and security and defence. The company was founded by Gordon Sanghera, Spike Willcocks and John Hagan Pryce Bayley in 2005 and is headquartered in Oxford, the United Kingdom.                                





 Details Hidden



KGB Text UK Ltd.

                                    KGB Text UK Ltd. provided mobile applications and information services. It offered answers for questions on various topics, including travel, restaurants, shopping, health, music, and sports. The company was founded by Sarah McVittie and Thomas Roberts in August 2003 and is headquartered in Cambridge, the United Kingdom.                                





