Company overview

Odey Asset Management LLP (‘Odey') is a leading London investment firm managing $12.2bn for institutional investors, private banks and individual investors across Global, European and UK strategies. The firm was established by Crispin Odey in 1991 to focus on active fund management with an equal emphasis on preserving capital and generating superior returns.
Odey has worked hard to build an investment team and client base committed to these principles and today continue to focus on performance rather than asset gathering. Of our 100 employees, over 35 are investment professionals and the firm's partners are amongst the largest investors in the strategies we run.
Odey is a well-established and respected company with a stable client base of over 2,500 investors. The firm continues to be independently owned by its 18 partners, thereby ensuring a strong alignment of interest with its clients.
In 2012 Odey formed a relationship with Copia Investment Partners to distribute their products exclusively in Australia to the institutional market. In 2014 Copia Investment Partners and Odey jointly set up the Australian based Odey International Fund for the retail market.
For more information visit the Odey website www.odey.com
















 








Crispin Odey - Founder at Odey Asset Management LLP



























































